# Enforce LF everywhere, on every platform and in CI, regardless of core.autocrlf.
#
# This is load-bearing, not cosmetic: the frozen vendored harness under
# src/vendored/ is byte-identical to the predecessor blobs (LF), and the CI hash
# tripwire (src/vendored/vendored_hashes.txt) is computed over those LF bytes. If a
# Windows checkout rewrote them to CRLF, every recorded SHA-256 would mismatch and
# the tripwire would false-fire on a clean clone. Golden fixtures must likewise stay
# byte-stable. So: normalize all text to LF in the repo and on checkout.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit, belt-and-suspenders, for the load-bearing paths:
src/vendored/** text eol=lf
tests/golden/*.json text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
uv.lock text eol=lf
